N2  - The article presents several commentaries concerning an article on relational view. The first article states that the while the article does an excellent job attempting to cover interorganizational relations and competitive factors of firms, that there is a need for discussion concerning the theory's position concerning existing theoretical approaches and perspectives. The second article states that there is a need to change the order of strategic processes and that the introduction of the relational view isn't meant to ignore existing conceptual foundations and their theoretical applications, but that it's not possible to just revise some of the principles to accommodate a relational view. It talks about using empirical research in studying international transaction costs.
AB  - The article presents several commentaries concerning an article on relational view. The first article states that the while the article does an excellent job attempting to cover interorganizational relations and competitive factors of firms, that there is a need for discussion concerning the theory's position concerning existing theoretical approaches and perspectives. The second article states that there is a need to change the order of strategic processes and that the introduction of the relational view isn't meant to ignore existing conceptual foundations and their theoretical applications, but that it's not possible to just revise some of the principles to accommodate a relational view. It talks about using empirical research in studying international transaction costs.
