TY  - JOUR
T1  - Ceo Charismatic Leadership: Levels-of-Management and Levels-of-Analysis Effects
AU  - Waldman, David A.
AU  - Yammarino, Francis J.
Y1  - 1999/04/01
PY  - 1999
DA  - 1999/04/01
N1  - doi: 10.5465/amr.1999.1893936
DO  - 10.5465/amr.1999.1893936
T2  - Academy of Management Review
JF  - Academy of Management Review
JO  - AMR
SP  - 266
EP  - 285
VL  - 24
IS  - 2
PB  - Academy of Management
N2  - We present a model of CEO charismatic leadership in organizations and show how such leadership can, through levels of management and analysis, impact organizational performance. We integrate levels issues relevant to the conceptualization of theoretical constructs and their relationships, measurement, and echelons, and develop the concept of close versus distant leadership as a means of understanding the dynamics of CEO leadership. We also include a consideration of possible alternative levels of analysis at which the constructs in our model may be operating.
AB  - We present a model of CEO charismatic leadership in organizations and show how such leadership can, through levels of management and analysis, impact organizational performance. We integrate levels issues relevant to the conceptualization of theoretical constructs and their relationships, measurement, and echelons, and develop the concept of close versus distant leadership as a means of understanding the dynamics of CEO leadership. We also include a consideration of possible alternative levels of analysis at which the constructs in our model may be operating.
